<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="775" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9527</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-17T17:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>839. From War Trade Board [for <persName corresp="#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                            <p>Replying to cables 744, 847 and 999.<note n="1" xml:id="d775fn1">No.
                                    744, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_779">p.
                                        779</ref>; Nos. 847 and 999 not printed.</note>
                            </p>
                            <list>
                                <label>(1)</label>
                                <item>Regarding matter of remittances of funds to Roumania, War
                                    Trade Board concurs with attitude taken by Foreign
                                    Office.</item>
                                <label>(2)</label>
                                <item>With reference to the matter of drawing no distinction in
                                    future between occupied and unoccupied Roumania, War Trade Board
                                    concurs insofar as affects matters within its
                                    jurisdiction.</item>
                                <label>(3)</label>
                                <item>Regarding expression of Allied determination to secure
                                    revision of Roumanian-German treaty at peace congress, War Trade
                                    Board feels this is matter entirely within jurisdiction of the
                                    State Department and must be answered by that Department.</item>
                            </list>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>